hopobject.body: Could I have a statement, please? black river falls pharmacy In the United States, suspicions over Huawei's close ties to the Chinese government have raised concerns over national security and Chinese espionage. Jim Lewis, a cybersecurity analyst, told "60 Minutes" last year that concerns over Huawei's close ties to the Chinese government caused the Obama administration to block what would have been the company's first American deal, a $5 billion contract to build Sprint's new 4G wireless network.
